README
## Getting Started with E2E testing solution -Playwright
- Build an image with [Dockerfile](Dockerfile) that contains a basic Docker configuration to build and start the project:
1. Download project from Github repository
2. Open a terminal
3. Go to the project root directory playwright.
4. Build image with:
```shell
docker build -t playwright-tests .
```
5. Run the project with the name or id of the created image
~~~ shell
 docker run playwright-tests  
~~~
# Perform these steps only for a new project
- Install libs locally
~~~shell
 npm init playwright@latest
~~~
- Available Scripts
In the project directory, you can run:
~~~shell
npx playwright test
~~~
- Other commands
Run your tests with UI Mode for a better developer experience with time travel debugging
~~~shell
npx playwright test --ui
~~~
View Report html with:
~~~shell
npx playwright show-report
~~~
Perform a debug with:
~~~shell
npx playwright test --debug
~~~
Run all browsers:
~~~shell
npx playwright test --browser=all
~~~
## Learn More
You can learn more in the [playwright documentation](https://playwright.dev/).